      <h1 class="h-title">Mykola Sudakov</h1>
      <p class="h-tagline">Research on Work and Social Transformations</p>

      <div class="h-meta">
        <div>PhD in Sociology · Associate Professor</div>
        <div>Academy of Labour, Social Relations and Tourism</div>
      </div>

      <p class="h-text">
        Research projects focus on structural changes in employment and labour markets, technological shifts, and emerging forms of work organisation.
      </p>
      <p class="h-text">
        An independent consulting practice specialises in the design of applied research, evaluation systems, and analytical solutions for national and international projects.
      </p>
      <p class="h-text">
        Teaching and training activities cover labour market studies, sociology of employment, research methodology, and applied analytics.
      </p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Research Interests</h2>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Structural transformations of employment and labour markets in the context of war and recovery</li>
        <li>Employment and education policies and programmes</li>
        <li>Employer demand for occupations and skills</li>
        <li>Skills development and human capital formation</li>
        <li>Graduate career trajectories and transitions from education to work (Tracer Studies)</li>
      </ul>
